   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER NINE GOD'S HISTORY IN TIME</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>GEN.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>1:1 REV.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>20:15 8 WORKING ON HIS ELECT</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>FROM ABRAHAM TO JOSEPH 4 WORKING ON ISAAC AND JACOB</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>WITH JOSEPH 2 Scripture Reading: Gen 32:24-32; 35:1-15; 47:7, 10-12, 27-31; 48:8-9, 15-16, 20; 49:28; 41:39-44, 55-57 OUTLINE Working on Jacob with Joseph: Having destined him to live a struggling life all his days: To escape from his uncle Laban according to the indication of the complaint of Laban's sons and the attitude of Laban, and according to God's instruction 31:1-21.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To face the trouble of Laban's pursuing and overtaking him while he was under the secret care and protection of God as the Angel of God Christ 31:10-13 31:22-55.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To face the trouble of his brother Esau's dealing with him 32:1-23; 33:1-17.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To wrestle even with God, who changed his name from Jacob to Israel, indicating that God would transform him from a supplanter Jacob to a wrestler with God or a prince of God Israel , and who made him limp 32:24-32.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>To face the trouble of the case of his daughter Dinah ch.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>34.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To be purified with his family from the foreign gods and their ornaments which they loved, according to God's commandment, that they might serve God with an altar built at Bethel, where God changed his name from Jacob to Israel and promised him that: He as the all-sufficient God would make him fruitful and multiplied; a nation and a company of nations would be of him, and kings would come out of his loins.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>He would give to him and his seed the land He gave to Abraham and Isaac 35:1-15.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To take care of the burial of Deborah, his mother Rebekah's nurse, without seeing his mother 35:8.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>To suffer the death of Rachel at the birth of Benoni the son of my sorrow, named by Rachel while dying at his birth , Benjamin the son of the right hand, named by Jacob the father 35:16-20.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To suffer his son Reuben's incest with his concubine Bilhah 35:22.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To suffer the loss of his beloved son Joseph ch.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>37.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>To suffer the danger of losing his son Simeon and his youngest son Benjamin 42:18 43:15; 44:9-34.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Releasing him from all his sufferings: To see his beloved son Joseph again in his honor and glory 45:1 47:12.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>To enjoy a rich and peaceful life with the worship to God at his old age 47:11-12, 27-31.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Causing him: To be transformed from a supplanter Jacob to a prince of God Israel 35:9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>To be matured to bless all people whom he contacted: To bless Pharaoh 47:7, 10.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>To bless Joseph with his two sons, Ephraim and Manasseh ch.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>48.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>To bless all his twelve sons 49:1-28.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Causing him, with Joseph: To go through a long period of suffering 37:4-36; 39:1-23; 40:12-15, 21-23; 41:9-37.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>To be exalted as the sovereign ruler 41:39-44: To rule over all of Egypt 45:8b-9a.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>To supply all the earth with food 41:55-57; 42:5-6.</S>
   </TEXT>
